parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause the vehicle to pull to one side, lose braking ability, or experience extended stopping distances, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side when applying brakes
the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal goes all the way down to the floor
the ABS warning light stays on
the brake pedal vibrates
the vehicle hops or skips when braking
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, experience extended stopping distances, or vibrate excessively, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ABS warning light stays on
the brake pedal vibrates
the vehicle hops or skips when braking
the brakes fail to stop the vehicle
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the ABS system operates with rapid pulsing of the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the vacuum brake booster can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, experience extended stopping distances, or vibrate excessively, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the brake pedal goes all the way down to the floor
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brake booster fails to provide adequate vacuum.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake line can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, experience extended stopping distances, or vibrate excessively, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the vehicle takes longer to stop

and potentially leading to fuel leaks.

" the vehicle is difficult to control
